\begin{theorem}[Solution of the non-homogeneous system - Duhamel formula / Variation of the constant]
    The Cauchy problem \(\begin{cases} X'(t) = A X(t) + F(t) \\ X(t_0) = X_0 \end{cases}\), where \(F\) is continuous,
    admits the following unique solution:
    \[ X(t) = e^{(t-t_0)A} X_0 + \int_{t_0}^t e^{(t-s)A} F(s) ds \]
\end{theorem}
